.hero
  %span.tag castle-rb 8.1 · rails
  %h1{ class: 'text-[2rem] mt-3' } Castle Rails example app
  %p.lead.mt-2
    A minimal Ruby on Rails + Devise application showing how to wire the
    = succeed '' do
      %a{ href: 'https://github.com/castle/castle-ruby' } castle-rb
    SDK into a real authentication flow.

.section-head
  %h2{ class: 'text-[1.2rem]' } What's demonstrated

%ul.prose-list.list-disc.pl-5
  %li
    %strong Sign up
    &mdash; new registrations are scored with the
    %code risk
    endpoint (<code>$registration</code>); a denied verdict rolls the sign-up back.
  %li
    %strong Login
    &mdash; successful logins are scored with the
    %code risk
    endpoint; failed logins go to
    %code filter
    and the verdict can allow, challenge or deny the user.
  %li
    %strong Logout, profile updates & custom events
    &mdash; recorded with the non-blocking
    %code log
    endpoint.
  %li
    %strong Webhooks
    &mdash; incoming Castle webhooks are signature-verified and listed under
    = link_to 'Webhooks', integrations_castle_webhooks_path

.section-head
  %h2{ class: 'text-[1.2rem]' } Configuration

%p
  Copy
  %code .env.example
  to
  %code .env
  and fill in your Castle credentials
  (<code>CASTLE_API_SECRET</code> and <code>CASTLE_PK</code>) from the
  = succeed '.' do
    %a{ href: 'https://dashboard.castle.io' } Castle dashboard
